&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Clinical Knee Fellow in Trauma &amp; Orthopaedics Department&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1x 6 month posts available &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;October 2021 - April 2022&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to be part of a long established knee fellowship programme comprising the management of both soft tissue and osteoarthritis conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the opportunity to develop your management and surgical skills in Knee Surgery. You will be required to attend out-patient sessions and participate in an on-call rota for general trauma. There will also be an opportunity to participate in Clinical Research Projects. The department prides itself on team-working and close collaboration with the clinical colleagues to provide a high quality Orthopaedic service. The fellowship post involves regular independent operating lists and clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A particular focus of the Fellowship is to allow significant exposure to Fixed Bearing Uni-compartmental Knee Replacement. Harrogate is a high volume centre and its results were recognised at the last GIRFT visit, being described as ‘Exemplary’. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You are encouraged to visit the hospital to meet our teams and experience the way we work. For more information or to arrange an informal visit please contact Professor Nicholas London or Mr David Duffy, both Consultants in Trauma and Orthopaedics on 01423 553750&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
